architecture efficient windows doors landscaping for heating cooling gray water & rainwater capture efficient landscaping overview simplicity carbon impact money savings health helper in the home the home may be the best place to begin to educate your family about making sustainable choices at home the biggest impact we have on the environment is through our use of energy and water many of the actions in the in the home section are small simple choices you can make in your everyday life such as setting your computer to sleep mode air drying your laundry or installing fluorescent light bulbs other choices have to do with periodic upkeep in your home such as installing weatherstripping cleaning your refrigerator coils or replacing furnace filters additionally there are some longer term decisions to keep in mind for when you want to upgrade your appliances or move to a new home we hope these ideas help you in your quest to make a more sustainable home fun facts for each section check here for additional fun information tips and quirky facts stanford university school of earth sciences stanford university home school of earth sciences home
